For the Greater Good is the eighth deluxe expansion for Call of Cthulhu: The Card Game. As the Agency reinforces and expands its network, roughly two-thirds of the expansion&rsquo;s 165 cards (three copies each of fifty-five different cards) lend new strength to the faction's heroic champions of law and order. Numerous police officers, military officials, investigators, and psychiatrists bolster the Government subtype, even as several new Hunter characters track the game&rsquo;s monsters and otherworldly evils across the earth, seeking to purge them from our world.

Of course, the confrontations of Call of Cthulhu: The Card Game are rife with violence and horror, so For the Greater Good grants Agency members access to plenty of new weapons and vehicles to aid them in their efforts. You&rsquo;ll find a host of new synergies between Agency subtypes, new gear, and powerful effects designed to renew the authority of law and order in a world tormented by burgeoning chaos. Moreover, as your Agency characters pursue their leads to all ends of the earth, you&rsquo;ll uncover several new conspiracies, each of which, if investigated, may help you safeguard humanity&rsquo;s future.

Polish your badges, grab your shotguns, and deputize the bravest and best of all the people close to you. While the world is threatened on all sides by ghouls, cultists, monsters, and Ancient Ones, humanity needs all the help it can get&hellip;

Guspira is a funny, quick and suitable board game for all ages, inspired on the world of fire, devils, beasts and everything related to a &lsquo;correfoc&rsquo;, one of the most gorgeous and spectacular fests of the Catalan culture. Among the game cards there are some characteristic elements of this celebration as &lsquo;Drac&rsquo;, &lsquo;V&iacute;bria&rsquo;, &lsquo;Guita&rsquo;, Devils or &lsquo;Tabalers&rsquo;, without forgetting &lsquo;correfocaires&rsquo;, brave people who jump and dance under the fire.

The main objective is to win the maximum number of &lsquo;correfocaires&rsquo; playing the pyrotechnic cards from the hand. But it is not always as easy as it seems to be, the dice has also its role&hellip;

Besides the playful side, Guspira is expected to be a way of promotion for the Catalan culture. The cards show the most characteristic elements of this celebration and they have no text in order to be played anywhere in the world.

A roll and move game with numbered spaces by Otto Maier Verlag. Players start at the first space and must follow the numbered spaces in towards the center space. First one to reach the end space is the winner.

The company published a similar game/similar equipment: Reise durch die Schweiz;
